97 (b) The director is authorized to take depositions and obtain discovery of any matter which
98 is not privileged and which is relevant to the subject matter involved in any proceeding or
99 petition before the commission in the same manner and subject to the same procedures
100 which would otherwise be applicable if such proceeding was then pending before a
101 superior court. The superior courts and the judges and clerks thereof are authorized to
102 issue all orders, injunctions, and subpoenas and to take all actions necessary to carry out
103 this subsection.
104 46-10-6.
105 The director is authorized to employ such assistants as he or she may need and is
106 authorized to employ or retain and fix the compensation of such consultants, expert
107 witnesses, accountants, engineers, attorneys, investigators, stenographers, or other technical
108 or clerical assistance, as may be necessary to carry out his or her duties; provided, however,
109 that no such employment shall occur nor shall any contracts for payment of fees or
110 expenses be paid for consultants, expert witnesses, accountants, engineers, attorneys,
111 investigators, stenographers, or other technical or clerical assistance unless such
112 employment or such contracts can be achieved using funds appropriated for such purposes.
113 The office shall keep suitable and proper records of all such expenditures. The
114 compensation of the director and such staff shall be paid from state funds appropriated to
115 the commission for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this chapter.
